<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-07-01T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-07-01T17:00:00-05:00" n="628" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d628">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/6319: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Canton</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-07-01T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 1,
                                        1925—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your June 26, 11 a.m. You should tactfully decline to sit on proposed
                            commission of inquiry unless officially requested to do so by the
                            British and French Consuls General and unless common foreign interests
                            would be furthered by your participation in which case you should
                            telegraph your views stating also the composition and defined objects of
                            the commission and await further instructions.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
